1
00:00:00,440 --> 00:00:02,110
(Child actors were accompanied
by a guardian...)

2
00:00:02,170 --> 00:00:03,840
(and filmed in a safe,
supervised environment.)

3
00:00:04,810 --> 00:00:06,680
Is this really what you wanted?

4
00:00:08,350 --> 00:00:11,150
Honey, what's wrong?

5
00:00:11,480 --> 00:00:14,750
Fine.
That video of my wife falling...

6
00:00:15,250 --> 00:00:16,620
I'm the one who posted it!

7
00:00:25,760 --> 00:00:29,430
- Hey, are you out of your mind?
- Honey!

8
00:00:29,500 --> 00:00:32,240
What on earth are you talking about?

9
00:00:32,670 --> 00:00:34,610
Did I hear you correctly?

10
00:00:35,440 --> 00:00:37,880
You posted the video of her falling
yourself?

11
00:00:38,440 --> 00:00:40,610
Don't tell me it was all staged.

12
00:00:41,650 --> 00:00:43,150
It wasn't him.

13
00:00:45,580 --> 00:00:46,650
I did it.

14
00:00:48,350 --> 00:00:49,520
- No way...
- What?

15
00:00:50,920 --> 00:00:53,120
Auntie, what is all this about?

16
00:00:53,890 --> 00:00:55,330
At this point, I have no idea.

17
00:00:56,830 --> 00:00:58,400
Eun Bin, let's go inside.

18
00:00:58,400 --> 00:01:02,130
Go inside? Are you kidding?
This is the best drama in ages.

19
00:01:03,970 --> 00:01:07,270
Did I hear that right?
What do you mean, it was staged?

20
00:01:08,110 --> 00:01:10,610
They posted that video of her fall
themselves?

21
00:01:11,380 --> 00:01:14,550
Mom...
I'll explain everything later.

22
00:01:17,580 --> 00:01:18,880
What are we going to do now?

23
00:01:21,220 --> 00:01:22,690
Way to go.

24
00:01:22,950 --> 00:01:25,320
Why hide it at all if you were
just going to blurt it out?

25
00:01:25,590 --> 00:01:27,060
This is what you wanted, isn't it?

26
00:01:27,530 --> 00:01:29,490
You kept pushing my buttons,
wanting me to snap.

27
00:01:29,560 --> 00:01:31,160
That's not true, you jerk!

28
00:01:31,660 --> 00:01:33,030
I forgave you.

29
00:01:33,300 --> 00:01:36,130
- I was trying to make up with you.
- Forgave me?

30
00:01:36,770 --> 00:01:39,740
Don't make me laugh.
A guy who wants to make up...

31
00:01:40,100 --> 00:01:43,810
meets with Councilor Hwang alone
and schemes with the producer?

32
00:01:44,040 --> 00:01:45,840
Hey, one minute you're saying...

33
00:01:46,240 --> 00:01:48,710
you don't need the nomination
or the show,

34
00:01:48,710 --> 00:01:49,710
and now you're mad about it?

35
00:01:50,680 --> 00:01:54,050
You know what?
Your apology was also insincere.

36
00:01:54,220 --> 00:01:57,290
Fine, man.
Think whatever you want, you jerk!

37
00:01:57,620 --> 00:01:59,420
You're not going to believe me
anyway!

38
00:01:59,420 --> 00:02:00,460
Why, you...

39
00:02:05,900 --> 00:02:07,370
Let's go home, Mother.

40
00:02:11,570 --> 00:02:12,970
Why would you...

41
00:02:13,710 --> 00:02:14,840
I'm afraid...

42
00:02:15,210 --> 00:02:18,880
- today isn't a good day for this.
- I am so sorry about all this.

43
00:02:20,750 --> 00:02:22,950
Ju Ah, go get your father.

44
00:02:23,380 --> 00:02:24,380
Okay.

45
00:02:26,350 --> 00:02:27,350
Let's go.

46
00:02:30,660 --> 00:02:33,530
Dad, please don't make a scene here.
Let's go inside. Okay?

47
00:02:33,930 --> 00:02:37,900
- It's not like that. You're wrong.
- Shut it, you punk!

48
00:02:38,330 --> 00:02:39,860
You're just as bad as he is,
you punk.

49
00:02:39,930 --> 00:02:43,500
Who are you yelling at, you coward?
Taking it out on my brother...

50
00:02:43,570 --> 00:02:45,700
- after you made him spy on me!
- That's a lie!

51
00:02:46,200 --> 00:02:48,970
This jerk volunteered to be a spy.

52
00:02:50,440 --> 00:02:53,550
Why? So you two could gang up on me
and find my weakness?

53
00:02:53,610 --> 00:02:55,280
Did you have fun tormenting me?

54
00:02:55,280 --> 00:02:59,550
Your victim complex is unbelievable.
Seriously.

55
00:02:59,820 --> 00:03:03,490
- It's pathetic. Truly pathetic!
- What did you say? You jerk!

56
00:03:03,820 --> 00:03:06,320
- Dad, please stop.
- What's gotten into you?

57
00:03:06,390 --> 00:03:08,790
- You think you can say anything?
- Dad, stop! Everyone's watching!

58
00:03:08,790 --> 00:03:10,600
Stop it already!
Let's just go home, come on.

59
00:03:11,060 --> 00:03:15,330
What? You're done being friends?
Fine! Me too, you jerk!

60
00:03:15,400 --> 00:03:16,670
Fine, you punk.
Don't be friends with me!

61
00:03:17,170 --> 00:03:18,170
Who asked you
to be my friend anyway?

62
00:03:18,240 --> 00:03:20,910
I'm done! I'm so sick
of your nonsense, you jerk!

63
00:03:20,910 --> 00:03:23,340
- Fine. Don't, you jerk!
- I won't! Get lost!

64
00:03:23,340 --> 00:03:24,910
- This scumbag!
- I said I won't, you punk!

65
00:03:24,980 --> 00:03:26,680
I've been patient with you,
but you've really crossed the line!

66
00:03:30,550 --> 00:03:34,920
See? I was right all along.
I knew something felt off.

67
00:03:35,220 --> 00:03:37,090
Dr. Yang's wife...

68
00:03:37,520 --> 00:03:40,190
After that video of her got posted,

69
00:03:40,460 --> 00:03:42,590
didn't you say
she even developed social anxiety?

70
00:03:43,130 --> 00:03:44,930
Exactly.

71
00:03:45,530 --> 00:03:47,900
I guess it was all just an act.

72
00:03:48,170 --> 00:03:50,570
My gosh, and to think...

73
00:03:50,970 --> 00:03:53,570
I invited them into our home.

74
00:03:54,040 --> 00:03:57,210
Tell me about it.
It's just ridiculous.

75
00:03:58,110 --> 00:03:59,110
And get this.

76
00:03:59,480 --> 00:04:02,010
It turns out we were the only ones
who didn't know.

77
00:04:02,350 --> 00:04:05,150
I know. They were probably scared
I'd cause a scene,

78
00:04:05,180 --> 00:04:06,520
so it seems
they hid everything from us.

79
00:04:08,690 --> 00:04:11,420
I really thought they'd made up
after 30 years.

80
00:04:11,990 --> 00:04:14,860
Jeong Han was so happy
hanging out with Bucket,

81
00:04:15,260 --> 00:04:18,400
but he must've been so sick about it
after he found out.

82
00:04:19,230 --> 00:04:21,200
How heartbroken he must have been.

83
00:04:27,910 --> 00:04:29,740
Dad, are you okay?

84
00:04:31,280 --> 00:04:32,940
Why wouldn't I be okay?

85
00:04:33,310 --> 00:04:37,050
I'm the fool for briefly forgetting
what a jerk he is. My gosh.

86
00:04:38,520 --> 00:04:40,080
What are we going to do now?

87
00:04:40,350 --> 00:04:43,790
Now that Mom and Grandma know,
things are going to blow up.

88
00:04:45,160 --> 00:04:47,860
Don't you worry. I'll handle it.

89
00:04:53,060 --> 00:04:56,430
(Damga Charcoal Grill)

90
00:04:58,000 --> 00:05:00,170
Look, man,
this is all a huge misunderstanding.

91
00:05:00,740 --> 00:05:01,740
Save it.

92
00:05:02,570 --> 00:05:03,570
Give it to me, you punk!

93
00:05:04,610 --> 00:05:06,740
Hey, when my brother
saw Councilor Hwang,

94
00:05:06,810 --> 00:05:08,750
do you have any idea
how much he talked you up?

95
00:05:09,110 --> 00:05:10,280
I said, forget it!

96
00:05:11,320 --> 00:05:12,350
None of that matters anymore.

97
00:05:12,880 --> 00:05:17,060
- I don't believe a word you say.
- What? Why not?

98
00:05:17,220 --> 00:05:21,560
You wouldn't answer my calls
or my questions,

99
00:05:21,730 --> 00:05:22,760
and you just kept messing with me.

100
00:05:22,830 --> 00:05:25,200
Because my brother said
he'd meet you and sort it out...

101
00:05:25,200 --> 00:05:28,170
- I said, forget it!
- My gosh, I'm losing my mind!

102
00:05:28,370 --> 00:05:30,800
- Just shut it and get out of here.
- Hey!

103
00:05:30,800 --> 00:05:32,200
Go on, you punk. Get lost.

104
00:05:33,500 --> 00:05:35,510
Why are you being so dismissive
when he's trying to talk to you?

105
00:05:35,910 --> 00:05:36,910
What did you say?

106
00:05:36,910 --> 00:05:39,340
He's trying to help.
Why are you being so mean to him?

107
00:05:39,410 --> 00:05:40,710
Dong Suk, stop.

108
00:05:40,850 --> 00:05:44,050
I'll talk to him.
What's wrong with you? Hey, it's me!

109
00:05:44,420 --> 00:05:48,820
- I'm your little brother, Dae Han.
- You're not my brother, you punk.

110
00:05:50,490 --> 00:05:51,560
Calm down, man.

111
00:05:51,990 --> 00:05:53,590
- Let go.
- Seriously, just calm down.

112
00:05:53,590 --> 00:05:55,090
- Let go.
- I'm sorry, man.

113
00:05:55,090 --> 00:05:57,330
- I said, let go!
- Look, I'm sorry. I...

114
00:05:57,330 --> 00:05:58,430
Let go!

115
00:05:59,330 --> 00:06:00,330
Dong Ik!

116
00:06:00,630 --> 00:06:03,840
Dad, have you lost your mind?
What gives you the right to do this?

117
00:06:03,840 --> 00:06:06,170
It's your sister's grand opening.
You're being completely out of line!

118
00:06:07,740 --> 00:06:09,140
Dae Han, are you okay?

119
00:06:17,050 --> 00:06:19,280
Eun Bin, go with your dad.
He's had way too much to drink.

120
00:06:19,480 --> 00:06:21,190
Gosh, seriously...

121
00:06:21,290 --> 00:06:24,120
My gosh, he's making such a scene.

122
00:06:25,260 --> 00:06:27,430
Woo Jae, take your uncle home
for the day, too.

123
00:06:27,730 --> 00:06:29,860
- Okay.
- Dong Suk.

124
00:06:33,160 --> 00:06:34,330
Dong Suk, I'm so sorry.

125
00:06:35,630 --> 00:06:37,370
What do you have to be sorry for?

126
00:06:37,940 --> 00:06:39,740
Your special day
is completely ruined.

127
00:06:40,240 --> 00:06:42,010
How is that your fault?

128
00:06:43,210 --> 00:06:46,540
I'm fine, so just go on home.
You too, Woo Jae.

129
00:06:46,980 --> 00:06:47,980
Okay.

130
00:06:50,920 --> 00:06:51,920
You stay here.

131
00:06:52,550 --> 00:06:53,920
Help her clean up, then come home.

132
00:06:54,720 --> 00:06:55,790
Okay.

133
00:07:01,990 --> 00:07:03,590
You invited all those guests,

134
00:07:04,600 --> 00:07:06,560
and this is the chaos that ensues?

135
00:07:07,270 --> 00:07:10,300
Father, it was all my fault.

136
00:07:10,940 --> 00:07:13,570
I made a terrible choice.

137
00:07:14,670 --> 00:07:15,810
No, that's not it.

138
00:07:16,310 --> 00:07:19,840
It's my fault, Grandpa.
I knew it all and tried to hide it.

139
00:07:20,610 --> 00:07:24,350
I should've dealt with it properly,
but I panicked and tried to hide it.

140
00:07:26,350 --> 00:07:29,320
I'm so ashamed
I can't even face Ms. Na.

141
00:07:30,660 --> 00:07:33,720
Regardless of your reasons,
you were in the wrong this time,

142
00:07:34,290 --> 00:07:35,660
so you will apologize to them.
No excuses.

143
00:07:36,590 --> 00:07:38,500
We have been, Father.

144
00:07:39,160 --> 00:07:42,570
But he wouldn't accept it,
and that just set Dong Ik off.

145
00:07:43,100 --> 00:07:44,840
That's a misunderstanding.

146
00:07:45,240 --> 00:07:49,110
Dr. Gong came to the restaurant
to make peace.

147
00:07:49,510 --> 00:07:51,340
My gosh, really?

148
00:07:52,180 --> 00:07:56,250
- You should have told me earlier.
- I'm sorry.

149
00:07:56,810 --> 00:07:58,520
I assumed you knew.

150
00:08:05,460 --> 00:08:07,760
Grandma, are you really upset?

151
00:08:08,660 --> 00:08:11,230
Upset? Why would I be?

152
00:08:12,660 --> 00:08:16,000
I feel like a clueless grandmother
who threw a party,

153
00:08:16,070 --> 00:08:18,340
not even knowing you were hurting.
I'm so ashamed.

154
00:08:18,500 --> 00:08:21,470
I didn't know back then either.
I only found out afterward.

155
00:08:21,940 --> 00:08:24,780
And once they made up,
everyone seemed so happy,

156
00:08:24,840 --> 00:08:27,350
I figured it was better
that you didn't know.

157
00:08:28,310 --> 00:08:30,410
I figured as much.

158
00:08:31,480 --> 00:08:34,890
Director Yang's parents didn't do it
to get me into trouble.

159
00:08:34,990 --> 00:08:38,160
And after they were found out,
they felt really terrible about it.

160
00:08:38,390 --> 00:08:41,430
And they apologized
to Dad over and over.

161
00:08:42,330 --> 00:08:45,100
But for things to have gone so wrong
again... I don't know.

162
00:08:46,960 --> 00:08:50,600
They'll make up again, won't they?
Right, Grandma?

163
00:08:52,270 --> 00:08:55,340
From what I saw today,
it won't be easy.

164
00:08:57,440 --> 00:08:58,440
I'm back.

165
00:08:58,580 --> 00:09:01,380
- Hey.
- Uncle, there wasn't another fight?

166
00:09:01,780 --> 00:09:04,480
A fight? No, we all just went
our separate ways.

167
00:09:04,920 --> 00:09:06,420
Right, Dae Han.

168
00:09:07,320 --> 00:09:10,520
You told me not to be surprised.
What was that about?

169
00:09:10,820 --> 00:09:11,960
Oh, right.

170
00:09:12,890 --> 00:09:13,990
It's just...

171
00:09:14,760 --> 00:09:15,760
It was nothing.

172
00:09:20,000 --> 00:09:21,600
What's with him now?

173
00:09:26,100 --> 00:09:30,370
- You're back?
- Yes. Ji Hu, let's go study.

174
00:09:31,480 --> 00:09:32,480
You got this!

175
00:09:33,110 --> 00:09:34,780
Oh, hey...

176
00:09:37,650 --> 00:09:40,480
By the way, Auntie,
where did you run off to earlier?

177
00:09:41,290 --> 00:09:43,490
What? Who said I ran off?

178
00:09:43,550 --> 00:09:47,360
You said you were going out
for wet wipes,

179
00:09:47,430 --> 00:09:49,260
but then you saw me following you
and ran off with your boyfriend,

180
00:09:49,260 --> 00:09:50,330
hand in hand!

181
00:09:50,530 --> 00:09:53,660
Don't be ridiculous.
I did no such thing.

182
00:09:54,530 --> 00:09:57,500
Then you could've brought the wipes.
You came back empty-handed.

183
00:09:57,570 --> 00:09:58,740
My gosh, shut it!

184
00:09:59,000 --> 00:10:02,840
Anyway, how's your dad holding up?
My goodness.

185
00:10:02,910 --> 00:10:06,240
He's the one who messed up,
but he's the one throwing a fit.

186
00:10:06,310 --> 00:10:09,710
My gosh, tell me about it.
Dad ruins everything.

187
00:10:09,810 --> 00:10:10,950
My gosh, honestly.

188
00:10:15,120 --> 00:10:17,250
Drink it, honey.
You'll ruin your stomach.

189
00:10:19,960 --> 00:10:21,290
Honey.

190
00:10:22,390 --> 00:10:23,390
I'm sorry.

191
00:10:24,400 --> 00:10:25,830
I messed everything up.

192
00:10:28,130 --> 00:10:29,330
No, you did the right thing.

193
00:10:30,770 --> 00:10:34,310
- The right thing?
- If you hadn't, I would have.

194
00:10:34,810 --> 00:10:37,980
No, really. You've put up
with more than enough.

195
00:10:38,240 --> 00:10:41,650
Even a worm will turn.
And you're a human being.

196
00:10:42,110 --> 00:10:43,110
You're right.

197
00:10:43,780 --> 00:10:45,050
I'm a human being, too.

198
00:10:45,820 --> 00:10:49,750
- I have my pride.
- Of course. A man must have pride.

199
00:10:50,550 --> 00:10:51,960
Honey, from now on,

200
00:10:52,220 --> 00:10:54,130
let's stop wasting
our emotional energy like this.

201
00:10:54,490 --> 00:10:58,800
Though it didn't work out,
you fought so hard for your goal.

202
00:11:01,300 --> 00:11:02,530
I truly...

203
00:11:03,300 --> 00:11:04,900
believe in you and respect you.

204
00:11:06,940 --> 00:11:08,040
Thank you.

205
00:11:09,210 --> 00:11:11,340
For always accepting me,
flaws and all,

206
00:11:12,380 --> 00:11:13,440
and for always being on my side.

207
00:11:21,150 --> 00:11:25,420
If you knew it was all staged
and planned to forgive him anyway,

208
00:11:25,760 --> 00:11:28,060
why didn't you just tell me that
from the start?

209
00:11:28,760 --> 00:11:33,500
Why risk a misunderstanding?
You know how simple Bucket can be.

210
00:11:36,170 --> 00:11:37,170
What?

211
00:11:38,070 --> 00:11:39,700
Is that it?

212
00:11:40,640 --> 00:11:41,640
What else?

213
00:11:42,340 --> 00:11:45,540
Come on, you're not mad
that I hid this from you?

214
00:11:45,940 --> 00:11:47,710
I'm not mad at you.

215
00:11:47,810 --> 00:11:52,420
Thank goodness.
I was terrified of you finding out.

216
00:11:53,980 --> 00:11:57,220
I didn't realize you meant Bucket
with the five stages of grief.

217
00:11:57,920 --> 00:12:00,290
I thought it might be depression
from male menopause...

218
00:12:00,290 --> 00:12:01,560
and almost wrote you a prescription.

219
00:12:02,630 --> 00:12:05,800
- You did?
- You must've been so stressed out.

220
00:12:05,860 --> 00:12:07,360
No wonder you had stomach cramps.

221
00:12:08,400 --> 00:12:11,840
Tell me about it.
I really thought I was going to die.

222
00:12:13,440 --> 00:12:14,710
But let me ask you one thing.

223
00:12:16,140 --> 00:12:19,010
Why did you decide
to forgive Bucket?

224
00:12:19,610 --> 00:12:22,850
Well... It's something Ju Ah said.

225
00:12:23,350 --> 00:12:26,250
She said forgiveness is
letting go for your own sake.

226
00:12:26,850 --> 00:12:29,550
Wait a minute.
That's what I always say.

227
00:12:29,750 --> 00:12:34,330
See? It proves I listen to you
even when you're not around.

228
00:12:34,390 --> 00:12:35,530
My goodness.

229
00:12:36,360 --> 00:12:38,000
Feel better now that
it's all out in the open?

230
00:12:38,330 --> 00:12:40,870
Yes. Seong Mi,
thanks for not being mad.

231
00:12:40,870 --> 00:12:42,000
I really appreciate it.

232
00:12:42,230 --> 00:12:43,370
Honestly.

233
00:12:44,840 --> 00:12:46,740
I guess I'm becoming
more big-hearted.

234
00:12:47,170 --> 00:12:48,610
Maybe it's because I'm getting old.

235
00:12:49,510 --> 00:12:51,710
Hey, you just had to get a jab in,
didn't you?

236
00:12:52,210 --> 00:12:56,450
Anyway, you said you were exhausted.
Did you end up getting that IV drip?

237
00:12:56,710 --> 00:12:59,820
- Yes. I went to see Yu Jin for it.
- Yu Jin? I see.

238
00:13:00,520 --> 00:13:05,090
How's she doing? Right.
Are her in-laws still a nightmare?

239
00:13:05,720 --> 00:13:06,720
Apparently so.

240
00:13:06,990 --> 00:13:08,960
She still goes on and on about
how much she envies me.

241
00:13:09,390 --> 00:13:12,400
I know, right?
In-laws like us are one of a kind.

242
00:13:13,200 --> 00:13:16,900
That's right. And there's no husband
quite like you, either. Right?

243
00:13:17,800 --> 00:13:19,570
No, there isn't.

244
00:13:20,100 --> 00:13:22,570
But what a relief. Thanks.

245
00:13:27,680 --> 00:13:29,310
Are you feeling that down?

246
00:13:30,350 --> 00:13:31,720
I guess I got my hopes up too high.

247
00:13:32,350 --> 00:13:36,150
I was really hoping to have a drink
with your father tonight.

248
00:13:36,990 --> 00:13:38,490
That day will come.

249
00:13:39,890 --> 00:13:43,460
- I don't know. Will it, really?
- Of course, it will.

250
00:13:43,960 --> 00:13:48,230
From now on, no matter what happens,
I'm never letting go of this hand.

251
00:13:53,170 --> 00:13:55,870
What?
You said you'd never let it go,

252
00:13:55,870 --> 00:13:57,440
and now you've changed your mind?

253
00:13:58,140 --> 00:13:59,140
Give it to me.

254
00:13:59,640 --> 00:14:00,640
Give you what?

255
00:14:00,980 --> 00:14:01,980
The ring.

256
00:14:02,480 --> 00:14:04,250
I heard you bought it
with Jun Hyeok.

257
00:14:04,720 --> 00:14:07,450
That Park Jun Hyeok.
Why did he have to go and say that?

258
00:14:09,090 --> 00:14:11,760
You won't be able to rest easy
until it's on my finger.

259
00:14:12,260 --> 00:14:14,990
This isn't how I wanted
to give it to you.

260
00:14:25,070 --> 00:14:27,970
It's so beautiful!
I absolutely love it.

261
00:14:28,840 --> 00:14:32,440
- You picked the perfect one.
- You're sure you're okay with this?

262
00:14:32,740 --> 00:14:34,350
I wanted to make it special.

263
00:14:34,410 --> 00:14:37,110
Every day is special
as long as we're together.

264
00:14:39,980 --> 00:14:41,220
You're right.

265
00:14:41,590 --> 00:14:46,160
It's a miracle we're even together.
I was getting ahead of myself.

266
00:14:47,520 --> 00:14:51,160
Thank you for facing
all these hardships with me.

267
00:15:03,740 --> 00:15:06,210
- You like it?
- I love it so much.

268
00:15:20,390 --> 00:15:21,390
Hey, Eun Bin.

269
00:15:22,390 --> 00:15:25,100
How's the mood over there?
Did your parents fight?

270
00:15:26,430 --> 00:15:27,460
I have no idea.

271
00:15:27,900 --> 00:15:31,800
By the way, why didn't you tell me
my mom staged the whole thing?

272
00:15:31,870 --> 00:15:32,900
You knew all about it, didn't you?

273
00:15:33,600 --> 00:15:36,340
What? What do you mean I knew?
I know nothing.

274
00:15:37,270 --> 00:15:41,010
Is the peace between our families
really over just like that?

275
00:15:41,450 --> 00:15:42,450
Beats me.

276
00:15:42,910 --> 00:15:44,520
It doesn't matter.

277
00:15:45,280 --> 00:15:48,420
No matter what crisis comes our way,
I'm not giving up on you.

278
00:15:49,120 --> 00:15:50,590
Hey, I have to go.

279
00:15:50,950 --> 00:15:52,120
Hey, wait, hold on!

280
00:15:53,220 --> 00:15:54,490
He hung up on me again.

281
00:15:55,090 --> 00:15:57,360
Go ahead. See if I let it get to me.

282
00:15:59,260 --> 00:16:01,270
The new wallpaper smell
in my room is gone.

283
00:16:01,270 --> 00:16:03,030
It's my last night sleeping here.

284
00:16:04,740 --> 00:16:07,200
So? What did you think of having
a front-row seat to the drama?

285
00:16:07,940 --> 00:16:10,010
I feel bad.
I'm not part of the family,

286
00:16:10,340 --> 00:16:12,440
and I ended up learning
all your personal family history.

287
00:16:12,740 --> 00:16:16,280
Hey, what are you talking about?
If you're here, you're family.

288
00:16:16,350 --> 00:16:18,280
Now that our paths have crossed
like this, we're family.

289
00:16:19,150 --> 00:16:20,180
You think so?

290
00:16:21,190 --> 00:16:25,420
My mom can be a bit much.

291
00:16:25,660 --> 00:16:28,130
She'd go through fire and water
for our family.

292
00:16:28,560 --> 00:16:30,090
I think she's really incredible.

293
00:16:30,790 --> 00:16:33,460
Especially in a world where
some parents abandon their own kids.

294
00:16:33,860 --> 00:16:34,870
Tell me about it.

295
00:16:34,870 --> 00:16:39,070
The women who gave birth to us...
They're heartless, aren't they?

296
00:16:42,370 --> 00:16:43,910
Does that upset you?

297
00:16:44,940 --> 00:16:47,580
I agree with you, too.

298
00:16:49,380 --> 00:16:53,150
The truth is, I used to be
very mean to my mom.

299
00:16:53,250 --> 00:16:54,350
Really?

300
00:16:54,890 --> 00:16:57,150
But she loves you so much. Why?

301
00:16:58,060 --> 00:17:02,660
My real mom left me, so I figured,
why would a stepmom be different?

302
00:17:04,090 --> 00:17:05,960
I never knew
when she might abandon me,

303
00:17:05,960 --> 00:17:09,100
so I purposely pushed her away
and treated her badly.

304
00:17:10,200 --> 00:17:13,270
I really don't think
your mom is like that at all.

305
00:17:13,970 --> 00:17:16,940
I know, right? You should see
how well she treats my brother.

306
00:17:20,480 --> 00:17:24,480
My gosh. You must be starving.
You haven't eaten a thing.

307
00:17:24,550 --> 00:17:25,920
I thought you'd left.

308
00:17:26,180 --> 00:17:28,620
I was so surprised when they said
you'd sleep in Grandpa's room.

309
00:17:29,190 --> 00:17:30,520
It's okay. Please have a seat.

310
00:17:30,990 --> 00:17:33,260
Why? Are you going to
lecture me again?

311
00:17:33,690 --> 00:17:34,690
No.

312
00:17:39,460 --> 00:17:40,860
Then why?

313
00:17:42,170 --> 00:17:43,370
I have a question for you.

314
00:17:44,370 --> 00:17:45,370
A question?

315
00:17:45,770 --> 00:17:46,770
Yes.

316
00:17:47,440 --> 00:17:51,340
To solve a problem, you need
to understand the root cause.

317
00:17:52,810 --> 00:17:53,910
It's about my father.

318
00:17:54,280 --> 00:17:57,410
Why on earth was he so determined
to be on "Human Theater?"

319
00:17:58,020 --> 00:17:59,780
Are his political ambitions
really that strong?

320
00:17:59,980 --> 00:18:03,320
Or does he actually want to be
some kind of mega-star?

321
00:18:06,190 --> 00:18:08,960
It wasn't just about that.

322
00:18:09,660 --> 00:18:12,330
Then what else is there?
Please just tell me.

323
00:18:18,100 --> 00:18:21,840
The "Human Theater" producer seemed
to only want our family on the show.

324
00:18:22,410 --> 00:18:25,310
What? But you two agreed
to do it together.

325
00:18:25,580 --> 00:18:27,780
That's not right.

326
00:18:28,250 --> 00:18:31,520
Hearing that, I can see why
Bucket would get the wrong idea.

327
00:18:32,250 --> 00:18:34,990
So now, it's awkward to try
and clear things up,

328
00:18:35,690 --> 00:18:38,760
and I'm thinking
I should just drop out.

329
00:18:39,720 --> 00:18:42,390
Why are you looking at me?
This is for you to figure out.

330
00:18:45,300 --> 00:18:48,230
But it's a contract.
You made a promise.

331
00:18:48,730 --> 00:18:51,570
She's right. Can't you just try
talking it out with them?

332
00:19:03,150 --> 00:19:06,180
This whole "Human Theater" thing,
just drop it.

333
00:19:06,980 --> 00:19:07,990
Just call it all off.

334
00:19:08,450 --> 00:19:10,350
Yes, I'll drop it.

335
00:19:11,090 --> 00:19:14,630
- I'll do as you say, Father.
- No, it's all a misunderstanding!

336
00:19:15,330 --> 00:19:17,660
Try and work things out
with Dr. Gong.

337
00:19:17,690 --> 00:19:20,200
I'm done bowing down to Jeong Han.

338
00:19:20,930 --> 00:19:23,770
Done bowing down? You're the one
who's in the wrong.

339
00:19:23,770 --> 00:19:25,440
Dad,
so if you're not doing the show,

340
00:19:25,470 --> 00:19:27,500
does that mean you're giving up
on running for city council, too?

341
00:19:27,870 --> 00:19:28,970
Why would I give that up?

342
00:19:29,840 --> 00:19:31,070
I'll do it on my own.

343
00:19:31,440 --> 00:19:35,250
- How will you do that? With what?
- Be quiet. I'll handle it.

344
00:19:35,510 --> 00:19:36,780
You're as stubborn as a mule.

345
00:19:37,050 --> 00:19:40,280
- Hey.
- Hyun Bin, you'll be late for work.

346
00:19:40,350 --> 00:19:41,420
Right.

347
00:19:47,460 --> 00:19:48,460
Gong Ju Ah.

348
00:19:51,730 --> 00:19:54,930
So you told your dad
to bury the whole issue.

349
00:19:55,300 --> 00:19:56,500
Was it because of Director Yang?

350
00:19:57,300 --> 00:20:00,600
- What?
- Are you afraid he'll penalize you?

351
00:20:01,100 --> 00:20:02,770
It's not like that.

352
00:20:03,640 --> 00:20:05,810
Mom, if you see him,
please don't say anything like that.

353
00:20:07,710 --> 00:20:10,510
Then why did you show up with him
at the grand opening yesterday?

354
00:20:11,420 --> 00:20:14,520
What's wrong with that?
We were going to the same event.

355
00:20:14,590 --> 00:20:17,550
- So we came together.
- And Jun Hyeok doesn't get jealous?

356
00:20:18,160 --> 00:20:19,390
You need to watch how you behave.

357
00:20:23,990 --> 00:20:25,300
Here, you drive today.

358
00:20:25,460 --> 00:20:27,860
I was planning on
taking the bus today.

359
00:20:28,500 --> 00:20:32,100
What? You should've left earlier.
Aren't you going to be late?

360
00:20:32,500 --> 00:20:34,970
Just get in.
I won't say another word.

361
00:20:35,510 --> 00:20:37,770
It's fine. I'll go by myself.
You go on ahead.

362
00:20:40,440 --> 00:20:43,210
I'm so tired,
and I just asked for one ride...

363
00:20:43,910 --> 00:20:45,420
That girl can be so cold.

364
00:21:09,770 --> 00:21:11,210
I'm here, babe!

365
00:21:28,990 --> 00:21:30,230
What's with the weird vibe?

366
00:21:32,430 --> 00:21:33,630
Don't tell me...

367
00:21:35,870 --> 00:21:37,970
Who was it? Who said it?

368
00:21:38,170 --> 00:21:40,570
Who started the rumor that
Director Yang and I are dating?

369
00:21:43,070 --> 00:21:44,070
Darn it.

370
00:21:45,640 --> 00:21:48,310
It was me. I started it.

371
00:21:49,080 --> 00:21:50,450
Vice President!

372
00:21:50,510 --> 00:21:53,250
What are you going to do
if Dr. Han finds out? Seriously.

373
00:21:53,450 --> 00:21:56,320
Sorry. I guess
I didn't think that far ahead.

374
00:21:56,590 --> 00:21:58,990
That was shortsighted of me.

375
00:21:59,520 --> 00:22:02,390
Dr. Han only visits
the Design Office,

376
00:22:02,390 --> 00:22:03,860
so make sure
the team doesn't tell her.

377
00:22:04,330 --> 00:22:06,930
Yes, I'll be sure to do just that.

378
00:22:12,770 --> 00:22:14,170
Oh, you're wearing the ring!

379
00:22:15,370 --> 00:22:17,840
What's this?
Did Pacu Nacho give you that ring?

380
00:22:17,940 --> 00:22:20,010
What is it? Tell me!
Hey! Is it a couple's ring?

381
00:22:20,080 --> 00:22:22,050
Let me see it, too!

382
00:22:32,720 --> 00:22:35,860
What is it? Did anything good happen
at your get-together yesterday?

383
00:22:36,090 --> 00:22:38,360
No, quite the opposite.

384
00:22:38,660 --> 00:22:40,300
The opposite? What do you mean?

385
00:22:43,600 --> 00:22:46,000
Go on. You promised you'd tell us.

386
00:22:46,370 --> 00:22:49,940
Talk now, or you know what I'll do.
I'll expose you two to Dr. Han.

387
00:22:52,680 --> 00:22:54,340
They found out.

388
00:22:55,410 --> 00:22:56,750
They found out? What do you mean?

389
00:22:57,880 --> 00:22:59,680
Both families found out...

390
00:22:59,820 --> 00:23:03,320
that my stepmother
posted the video herself.

391
00:23:03,450 --> 00:23:04,450
Seriously?

392
00:23:05,390 --> 00:23:07,090
And? What happened?

393
00:23:07,090 --> 00:23:09,990
- Did your moms fight or what?
- Hey, watch it.

394
00:23:12,160 --> 00:23:15,830
- Sorry.
- Thankfully, it wasn't that bad.

395
00:23:16,670 --> 00:23:20,400
Man, this is a real mess.
Facing Dr. Han will be awkward.

396
00:23:20,870 --> 00:23:23,710
Gosh, how much longer must I pretend
to be Gong Ju Ah's boyfriend?

397
00:23:24,170 --> 00:23:26,340
Sorry. It is what it is.

398
00:23:28,110 --> 00:23:30,350
You have to find a way
to make them reconcile.

399
00:23:31,310 --> 00:23:32,680
Are you just going to give up
like this?

400
00:23:34,120 --> 00:23:37,120
No, but I actually
have to be somewhere.

401
00:23:39,020 --> 00:23:40,520
I asked
if you're just going to give up.

402
00:23:40,860 --> 00:23:42,260
The one and only Pacu Nacho?

403
00:23:43,460 --> 00:23:44,490
Hey, what are you going to do?

404
00:23:44,960 --> 00:23:46,830
Is there any sign that
the families could reconcile?

405
00:23:47,060 --> 00:23:51,000
I don't know. Right now,
there's just no solution in sight.

406
00:23:53,740 --> 00:23:56,040
Hey, Nurse Oh! Dae Han!

407
00:23:59,840 --> 00:24:00,910
Oh, for Pete's sake.

408
00:24:04,880 --> 00:24:07,120
I can't believe this.

409
00:24:07,550 --> 00:24:10,320
So much for making up.
Things completely fell apart.

410
00:24:10,750 --> 00:24:14,360
- So, what now? What's our plan B?
- I've got nothing!

411
00:24:15,690 --> 00:24:16,760
Darn...

412
00:24:18,930 --> 00:24:22,970
But you... By any chance,
are you and Officer Jung...

413
00:24:23,800 --> 00:24:24,970
secretly dating? You are, right?

414
00:24:25,440 --> 00:24:27,570
Excuse me?
Where is this coming from?

415
00:24:27,570 --> 00:24:31,040
I figured you were prickly with him
to hide that you're dating.

416
00:24:32,080 --> 00:24:33,880
No, I was genuinely being prickly.

417
00:24:34,340 --> 00:24:37,580
And here I was thinking...
A while ago, Officer Jung said...

418
00:24:37,650 --> 00:24:41,150
his heart was racing for someone,
and I thought that person...

419
00:24:41,380 --> 00:24:43,550
- might be you.
- He said that?

420
00:24:45,490 --> 00:24:47,260
So there was another woman.

421
00:24:47,590 --> 00:24:50,660
No wonder he shot me down so hard.
My gosh.

422
00:24:51,060 --> 00:24:52,060
What was that?

423
00:24:53,000 --> 00:24:57,270
- You got rejected?
- Yes. When he rescued me,

424
00:24:57,330 --> 00:24:59,970
- I fell for him, so I made my move.
- Okay.

425
00:24:59,970 --> 00:25:03,340
- He rejected my gift and a date.
- My gosh!

426
00:25:05,280 --> 00:25:07,940
Hey, listen.
It might just be a misunderstanding.

427
00:25:08,010 --> 00:25:10,050
I thought
Dong Suk was with another guy,

428
00:25:10,050 --> 00:25:11,880
but it turned out it was me.

429
00:25:12,350 --> 00:25:14,920
Excuse me?
Should you be giving me advice now?

430
00:25:15,150 --> 00:25:17,220
Why don't you worry about
your own future?

431
00:25:17,290 --> 00:25:19,390
You're right.
I shouldn't have been so nosy.

432
00:25:19,590 --> 00:25:22,030
You're the one
who should be dating in secret.

433
00:25:22,460 --> 00:25:23,460
I can't.

434
00:25:24,160 --> 00:25:28,000
Dong Suk said she'd only date me
if both our families approve.

435
00:25:31,430 --> 00:25:35,040
That sounds like
it'll be next to impossible.

436
00:25:41,610 --> 00:25:43,110
My children have truly...

437
00:25:43,610 --> 00:25:45,650
been terribly rude.

438
00:25:46,950 --> 00:25:48,920
What's done is done.

439
00:25:50,250 --> 00:25:51,890
It just kept escalating.

440
00:25:52,820 --> 00:25:55,390
I can see how it would've been
difficult to handle.

441
00:25:56,390 --> 00:25:57,390
You see,

442
00:25:57,960 --> 00:26:01,460
when my daughter-in-law,
Hyun Bin and Eun Bin's mom, left...

443
00:26:02,070 --> 00:26:05,170
I was so filled with rage,
I stopped speaking completely.

444
00:26:05,370 --> 00:26:08,940
It was Se Ri
who got me to speak again.

445
00:26:10,840 --> 00:26:12,980
Whether I was listening or not,

446
00:26:13,040 --> 00:26:16,050
Se Ri just kept on talking to me.

447
00:26:18,350 --> 00:26:20,580
She grew up an orphan,

448
00:26:20,680 --> 00:26:23,590
but her heart was
just so full of love.

449
00:26:24,220 --> 00:26:26,520
Those kids weren't even her own,

450
00:26:26,690 --> 00:26:29,360
but she absolutely doted on them.

451
00:26:30,090 --> 00:26:33,100
And the one who made a man
out of my good-for-nothing son...

452
00:26:33,660 --> 00:26:35,230
was also Se Ri.

453
00:26:39,670 --> 00:26:40,870
So, as you can imagine,

454
00:26:41,840 --> 00:26:45,740
I came to cherish and adore Se Ri.

455
00:26:46,580 --> 00:26:51,150
So I trusted her, protected her,
and took her side no matter what,

456
00:26:52,380 --> 00:26:54,320
and eventually,
she crossed the line.

457
00:26:56,520 --> 00:26:58,020
It's all my fault.

458
00:26:59,190 --> 00:27:02,230
I know exactly how you feel.

459
00:27:02,930 --> 00:27:06,860
My daughter-in-law is
the apple of my eye, too.

460
00:27:08,100 --> 00:27:09,400
Our Se Ri...

461
00:27:11,030 --> 00:27:13,770
I wish she'd had a mother like you.

462
00:27:14,500 --> 00:27:17,240
But she doesn't, so what can you do?

463
00:27:17,640 --> 00:27:20,180
I have to be a father to her
and give her all my love.

464
00:27:23,110 --> 00:27:25,580
You were so kind to invite us over,

465
00:27:25,920 --> 00:27:27,480
and you even served us
that wonderful steamed sea bream.

466
00:27:30,820 --> 00:27:34,590
I feel so ashamed and uncomfortable.

467
00:27:35,530 --> 00:27:36,830
Even so,

468
00:27:38,160 --> 00:27:40,600
it's been a while since
we had such a nice time,

469
00:27:41,660 --> 00:27:43,470
so I'll choose
to remember it fondly.

470
00:27:49,910 --> 00:27:50,910
Yes.

471
00:27:51,540 --> 00:27:55,080
- Doctor, your next patient is here.
- Okay, got it.

472
00:28:00,650 --> 00:28:02,290
I'm here for a therapy session.

473
00:28:03,790 --> 00:28:05,390
What is this all of a sudden?

474
00:28:06,120 --> 00:28:09,390
I was afraid you'd turn me down
if I just showed up or pestered you.

475
00:28:11,490 --> 00:28:15,030
I made an appointment and came,
but you don't look happy to see me.

476
00:28:18,170 --> 00:28:19,200
Just say what you came to say.

477
00:28:19,940 --> 00:28:24,540
By the time I learned everything,
it was too late for me to speak up.

478
00:28:24,970 --> 00:28:26,580
On behalf of my parents,

479
00:28:26,640 --> 00:28:30,010
I'd like to sincerely apologize
to you and your family.

480
00:28:33,480 --> 00:28:34,580
And?

481
00:28:34,920 --> 00:28:38,050
Are you here to ask for forgiveness,
or to make up, or something?

482
00:28:39,560 --> 00:28:40,890
Yesterday, my stepmother...

483
00:28:41,890 --> 00:28:44,030
told me why my father
was pushing himself so hard,

484
00:28:44,090 --> 00:28:46,960
why he was trying so desperately
to be on that show.

485
00:28:48,570 --> 00:28:50,000
Your father...

486
00:28:50,670 --> 00:28:54,570
wanted to go on that show
to show your biological mother...

487
00:28:55,040 --> 00:28:58,680
how well you both turned out.

488
00:29:00,180 --> 00:29:02,610
And your grandmother
who left 30 years ago...

489
00:29:02,680 --> 00:29:05,350
I think he believed she'd see it,
wherever she is.

490
00:29:07,220 --> 00:29:10,850
And Dr. Gong
probably had a similar reason.

491
00:29:10,850 --> 00:29:12,320
I think that's why
he decided to do the show,

492
00:29:12,320 --> 00:29:15,060
even though he had to give up
his plan to move.

493
00:29:17,730 --> 00:29:18,730
That's right.

494
00:29:19,160 --> 00:29:23,170
I think they're so busy fighting,
they forgot why they started.

495
00:29:23,400 --> 00:29:27,670
I know I have no right to ask,
but I came to ask you to remind him.

496
00:29:33,810 --> 00:29:34,810
Yes, Producer.

497
00:29:35,580 --> 00:29:37,550
No, I'm fine.

498
00:29:38,480 --> 00:29:39,950
As you mentioned yesterday,

499
00:29:40,350 --> 00:29:42,190
go ahead with Dr. Gong's family.

500
00:29:43,290 --> 00:29:45,620
As for my family,

501
00:29:45,890 --> 00:29:48,120
we've decided
we won't be on the show.

502
00:29:48,120 --> 00:29:49,160
(Korean Medicine Doctor
Yang Dong Ik)

503
00:29:49,160 --> 00:29:50,160
No.

504
00:29:50,530 --> 00:29:52,500
No, don't worry.
I'm not taking it the wrong way.

505
00:29:55,400 --> 00:29:56,400
What was that?

506
00:29:57,330 --> 00:30:01,040
Dr. Gong said he'll drop it
if I'm not on the show?

507
00:30:07,780 --> 00:30:11,680
This young radish kimchi is great.
Should I take some to Dr. Yang?

508
00:30:12,080 --> 00:30:13,750
Oh, should we do that?

509
00:30:14,120 --> 00:30:15,150
Don't bother.

510
00:30:16,090 --> 00:30:20,120
Hey, where did Mom go?
She didn't even eat.

511
00:30:20,390 --> 00:30:21,820
(Damga Charcoal Grill)

512
00:30:21,890 --> 00:30:23,060
(Endorphin)

513
00:30:24,590 --> 00:30:26,560
- Hello.
- Thanks.

514
00:30:32,400 --> 00:30:33,970
Congratulations
on the grand opening.

515
00:30:35,140 --> 00:30:37,810
I didn't get to say hi yesterday,
and...

516
00:30:38,540 --> 00:30:40,940
I had something
I wanted to give you.

517
00:30:43,750 --> 00:30:45,550
What's all this?

518
00:30:45,880 --> 00:30:48,990
Your hands will get wet a lot,
and you'll be on your feet,

519
00:30:49,820 --> 00:30:53,860
so I packed some eczema cream
and compression bands for you.

520
00:30:55,290 --> 00:30:56,390
Thank you so much.

521
00:30:58,460 --> 00:31:02,870
You can talk to me casually
like you used to.

522
00:31:04,670 --> 00:31:05,670
Okay.

523
00:31:06,200 --> 00:31:09,210
You were upset about my brother
and Se Ri, weren't you?

524
00:31:10,340 --> 00:31:11,570
I'm so sorry.

525
00:31:13,710 --> 00:31:17,110
Your father already apologized
to me for that.

526
00:31:18,250 --> 00:31:19,250
My father did?

527
00:31:22,350 --> 00:31:23,450
But more importantly,

528
00:31:24,190 --> 00:31:25,990
if I ever got the chance,

529
00:31:26,360 --> 00:31:28,220
there was something
I've been meaning to tell you.

530
00:31:30,960 --> 00:31:33,760
About the pain you went through
because of my son's ex-wife...

531
00:31:34,960 --> 00:31:36,270
I'm really sorry about that.

532
00:31:37,700 --> 00:31:39,440
No, please.

533
00:31:40,000 --> 00:31:41,270
Why would you apologize?

534
00:31:42,840 --> 00:31:45,170
To have something like this happen
in our family again...

535
00:31:45,810 --> 00:31:47,380
It just broke my heart.

536
00:31:48,240 --> 00:31:50,680
I'm really okay now, honestly.

537
00:31:51,350 --> 00:31:52,350
Good.

538
00:31:53,350 --> 00:31:55,220
I heard you met someone special.

539
00:31:56,550 --> 00:31:57,590
Maybe that's why...

540
00:31:58,190 --> 00:32:00,320
you look so much brighter
and more beautiful.

541
00:32:03,690 --> 00:32:06,260
My son, Dae Han,
has met someone new, too.

542
00:32:06,800 --> 00:32:08,630
So please, don't worry about him.

543
00:32:09,230 --> 00:32:10,230
After everything...

544
00:32:11,070 --> 00:32:12,900
you've been through,

545
00:32:13,400 --> 00:32:14,940
I hope
you can put the past behind you...

546
00:32:15,570 --> 00:32:17,110
and be truly loved.

547
00:32:17,770 --> 00:32:19,540
I just want you to be happy.

548
00:32:22,250 --> 00:32:23,250
I will.

549
00:32:28,520 --> 00:32:32,360
The pharmacist visited
the restaurant and gave her a gift.

550
00:32:33,020 --> 00:32:34,020
She did?

551
00:32:34,090 --> 00:32:37,730
Yes. Now your sister's all over me
to get you to change your mind.

552
00:32:38,090 --> 00:32:40,500
I don't get why she's so worked up.
It has nothing to do with her.

553
00:32:41,930 --> 00:32:42,970
Listen, Se Ri.

554
00:32:43,970 --> 00:32:46,270
I got a call
from the "Human Theater" producer.

555
00:32:47,470 --> 00:32:48,470
And?

556
00:32:49,140 --> 00:32:50,810
It looks like I misunderstood.

557
00:32:51,570 --> 00:32:53,580
He said Jeong Han won't do it
if I don't.

558
00:32:54,910 --> 00:32:55,980
See? I knew it.

559
00:32:56,450 --> 00:32:59,080
Hyun Bin said
you had it all wrong, too.

560
00:33:00,650 --> 00:33:03,320
I can't just go back and agree now.
What am I supposed to do?

561
00:33:03,450 --> 00:33:05,820
Right? That would be a bit awkward,
wouldn't it?

562
00:33:06,090 --> 00:33:07,090
Yes, it would.

563
00:33:07,660 --> 00:33:08,930
How many times does this make?

564
00:33:11,690 --> 00:33:12,700
My gosh.

565
00:33:13,260 --> 00:33:16,270
- Oh, my goodness!
- What? Who is it?

566
00:33:21,970 --> 00:33:24,470
Wait, Bucket's son came to see you?

567
00:33:25,340 --> 00:33:27,880
- He did.
- So what did he want?

568
00:33:29,250 --> 00:33:30,250
Honey.

569
00:33:30,780 --> 00:33:34,220
Do you remember why you wanted
to be on "Human Theater?"

570
00:33:34,950 --> 00:33:36,820
Yes, of course.

571
00:33:38,020 --> 00:33:41,220
Since a lot of older people
watch "Human Theater,"

572
00:33:42,330 --> 00:33:43,330
I thought that wherever he is,

573
00:33:44,090 --> 00:33:47,060
my father might happen to see it.

574
00:33:48,600 --> 00:33:49,600
Why do you ask?

575
00:33:50,470 --> 00:33:52,400
Then just focus on that
and follow me.

576
00:33:52,700 --> 00:33:53,700
There's somewhere we need to be.

577
00:33:54,270 --> 00:33:56,170
What? Where are we going?

578
00:34:03,580 --> 00:34:05,250
Why did you want to see us?

579
00:34:05,950 --> 00:34:08,320
What, am I supposed to apologize
or something?

580
00:34:09,650 --> 00:34:13,890
I have no interest in an apology
completely devoid of remorse.

581
00:34:14,290 --> 00:34:17,730
You wouldn't mean it,
and I don't intend to forgive you.

582
00:34:18,290 --> 00:34:22,530
- So you called us here for a fight?
- Enough.

583
00:34:24,300 --> 00:34:25,600
Yang Dong Ik. Gong Jeong Han.

584
00:34:28,740 --> 00:34:29,740
Both of you...

585
00:34:33,640 --> 00:34:34,810
You will appear on "Human Theater."

586
00:34:35,550 --> 00:34:37,710
- What?
- Seong Mi.

587
00:34:37,710 --> 00:34:40,850
You both remember why you agreed
to do this show, right?

588
00:34:43,520 --> 00:34:46,160
How much longer are you going
to go back and forth on this?

589
00:34:46,860 --> 00:34:49,590
You both signed the contract,
so just do it. Both of you.

590
00:34:49,590 --> 00:34:51,530
- Got it?
- My gosh, Doctor.

591
00:34:51,990 --> 00:34:55,200
- That's not the right way to do it.
- And what isn't?

592
00:34:55,670 --> 00:35:00,200
If you're the one who wants this,
you should be asking us nicely.

593
00:35:00,270 --> 00:35:01,270
Isn't that right, honey?

594
00:35:02,340 --> 00:35:03,940
Honey, I...

595
00:35:04,910 --> 00:35:07,110
It wasn't me. It was your son.

596
00:35:07,540 --> 00:35:09,780
It was Director Yang who asked.

597
00:35:09,780 --> 00:35:11,580
- My gosh. Hyun Bin did?
- What? Hyun Bin?

598
00:35:12,010 --> 00:35:14,620
Forget all this talk about
making up and apologies.

599
00:35:15,080 --> 00:35:16,090
Treat it like business.

600
00:35:17,020 --> 00:35:21,560
So you mean,
like a friendship for show?

601
00:35:21,760 --> 00:35:23,630
I don't feel like dragging this out.

602
00:35:24,330 --> 00:35:26,460
Are you in or out? I need an answer.

603
00:35:40,640 --> 00:35:42,850
We'll do it. Of course.

604
00:35:43,810 --> 00:35:44,810
You do it, too.

605
00:35:47,220 --> 00:35:48,550
Come on, seriously...

606
00:35:49,050 --> 00:35:50,290
Please do it, Dr. Gong.

607
00:35:50,590 --> 00:35:52,960
My husband saved your life,
didn't he?

608
00:35:55,020 --> 00:35:56,730
That wasn't all staged, was it?

609
00:35:58,060 --> 00:36:01,000
- What?
- Why? I'd say it's a fair doubt.

610
00:36:03,200 --> 00:36:06,170
Seong Mi, I can't believe
even you would doubt my sincerity.

611
00:36:06,500 --> 00:36:08,070
How could I not?

612
00:36:09,170 --> 00:36:10,570
This isn't the first time,
after all.

613
00:36:11,240 --> 00:36:15,240
My, Doctor! Bringing up the past
is such a cowardly move, isn't it?

614
00:36:15,510 --> 00:36:17,750
Fine. I'm a coward.

615
00:36:18,750 --> 00:36:22,150
And you're a textbook Machiavellian.

616
00:36:23,720 --> 00:36:26,720
I'm just too uneducated to know
what you're talking about.

617
00:36:27,020 --> 00:36:29,190
It's someone who manipulates others
to achieve their goals...

618
00:36:29,860 --> 00:36:33,660
and prioritizes results
over morality.

619
00:36:37,770 --> 00:36:38,870
I'll take that as a compliment.

620
00:36:40,140 --> 00:36:41,200
You. Are you in or out?

621
00:36:46,040 --> 00:36:47,940
Fine, okay, I'll do it.

622
00:36:48,580 --> 00:36:49,580
Hey.

623
00:36:49,880 --> 00:36:52,680
But when this shoot is over,
we're really done. Got it?

624
00:36:53,120 --> 00:36:55,890
I'm never dealing with you again.

625
00:36:56,150 --> 00:36:57,690
That's exactly what I wanted,
you jerk.

626
00:36:59,390 --> 00:37:00,390
Darn you...

627
00:37:00,720 --> 00:37:02,060
- My gosh!
- Get out of my way!

628
00:37:02,060 --> 00:37:03,460
- Move! I got up first!
- Step aside!

629
00:37:03,530 --> 00:37:04,530
Unbelievable!

630
00:37:10,970 --> 00:37:12,000
Let me give you a warning.

631
00:37:12,900 --> 00:37:15,200
If you try to pull a fast one
even one more time,

632
00:37:15,940 --> 00:37:17,570
I will not let it slide.

633
00:37:18,940 --> 00:37:21,110
Okay. You do that.

634
00:37:21,480 --> 00:37:24,150
- So, what, should we shake on it?
- I don't think so.

635
00:37:32,920 --> 00:37:35,190
This is perfect! Absolutely perfect.

636
00:37:35,460 --> 00:37:37,660
Oh, my son!
I'm so grateful to my son.

637
00:37:38,660 --> 00:37:39,660
Oh, this is great.

638
00:37:40,200 --> 00:37:42,060
So you've decided to resume filming?

639
00:37:42,570 --> 00:37:46,940
I wasn't thrilled about it,
but they were the ones who insisted.

640
00:37:47,840 --> 00:37:50,010
And can you believe it was Hyun Bin
who went and asked them?

641
00:37:50,810 --> 00:37:51,810
Hyun Bin did?

642
00:37:52,170 --> 00:37:54,710
Yes. When my own son
goes to such lengths...

643
00:37:55,410 --> 00:37:57,450
As a father, I have to
live up to my child's expectations,

644
00:37:58,150 --> 00:37:59,350
wouldn't you say?

645
00:38:02,150 --> 00:38:05,050
So Hyun Bin is finally acting
like a dutiful son.

646
00:38:09,290 --> 00:38:12,560
Director Yang?
Director Yang came to see you?

647
00:38:13,230 --> 00:38:16,530
Yes. He came and asked me
to talk them into it.

648
00:38:16,600 --> 00:38:20,270
Oh, good. Let's quit the tug-of-war
and just get it over with.

649
00:38:20,700 --> 00:38:25,240
I know, right? Gosh, how many times
have they gone back and forth?

650
00:38:29,050 --> 00:38:30,550
Why is she so happy about this?

651
00:38:30,810 --> 00:38:31,810
Beats me.

652
00:38:35,550 --> 00:38:37,390
Are you sure
this is the right place?

653
00:38:38,190 --> 00:38:39,420
Looks like it.

654
00:38:40,920 --> 00:38:44,990
So, when were you going to tell me?
It's been days and not a word.

655
00:38:45,130 --> 00:38:46,130
Tell you what?

656
00:38:48,000 --> 00:38:51,930
About you secretly seeing my mom
to convince our dads to do the show.

657
00:38:52,100 --> 00:38:54,500
- I did good, right?
- You did great, Yang Hyun Bin!

658
00:38:54,600 --> 00:38:56,310
Well done!

659
00:38:57,210 --> 00:38:59,580
- You really did a great job.
- I'm great at everything.

660
00:38:59,980 --> 00:39:01,280
Of course, you are.

661
00:39:03,210 --> 00:39:04,250
Seriously.

662
00:39:05,180 --> 00:39:07,250
- My gosh.
- Hey, what are you doing?

663
00:39:07,250 --> 00:39:08,850
Why are you taking our picture
without even asking us?

664
00:39:09,020 --> 00:39:10,420
I'm adding
a picture of my favorite couple...

665
00:39:10,420 --> 00:39:11,520
to my collection. Why?

666
00:39:11,690 --> 00:39:15,660
By the way, Vice President,
why did you call us on a weekend?

667
00:39:15,760 --> 00:39:20,130
I thought you were at the hospital
all weekend on caregiver duty.

668
00:39:20,330 --> 00:39:23,230
That's because the Chairman found
a caregiver he actually likes.

669
00:39:23,770 --> 00:39:27,540
So with that person on duty,
the VP has earned her freedom.

670
00:39:28,700 --> 00:39:30,670
We need to have a very
important meeting today.

671
00:39:31,040 --> 00:39:33,980
- A meeting?
- Let's fix the fake boyfriend mess.

672
00:39:34,980 --> 00:39:36,510
There you go again,
making things up.

673
00:39:37,450 --> 00:39:38,750
See? I told you we'd get caught.

674
00:39:39,820 --> 00:39:41,920
The thing is,
on "Love Signal" this week,

675
00:39:41,980 --> 00:39:44,320
Yoon Se Rin and Kang Min Jae
had a date at the Han River.

676
00:39:45,290 --> 00:39:47,020
And she wanted to try it out.

677
00:39:47,390 --> 00:39:49,460
A Han River experience.
This is so exciting!

678
00:39:52,930 --> 00:39:55,030
What? Give me a break.

679
00:40:02,070 --> 00:40:03,070
Nice!

680
00:40:05,710 --> 00:40:06,710
This is nice.

681
00:40:08,210 --> 00:40:09,380
Am I going too fast?

682
00:40:18,420 --> 00:40:19,420
Is it good?

683
00:40:19,820 --> 00:40:21,420
Go!

684
00:40:23,730 --> 00:40:25,530
My gosh, how does this thing work?

685
00:40:26,160 --> 00:40:27,660
- Oh, no!
- My goodness.

686
00:40:30,130 --> 00:40:31,130
What's going on?

687
00:40:32,870 --> 00:40:34,000
This is so fun!

688
00:40:40,580 --> 00:40:41,910
So this is what chicken
by the Han River is like.

689
00:40:42,340 --> 00:40:45,080
- You have fun like this without me.
- What?

690
00:40:45,950 --> 00:40:47,120
Fun? Hardly.

691
00:40:47,480 --> 00:40:50,650
I thought the VP's "guy friend"
meant living it up. What is this?

692
00:40:50,720 --> 00:40:51,850
What's wrong with
the Han River experience?

693
00:40:52,560 --> 00:40:54,720
You don't even have a girlfriend.
You should be grateful I'm with you.

694
00:40:55,760 --> 00:40:57,660
But wait, you two...

695
00:40:58,430 --> 00:40:59,760
Are you two really just friends?

696
00:41:01,560 --> 00:41:02,570
Come on, Director.

697
00:41:02,900 --> 00:41:05,230
How could you say something
so scandalous?

698
00:41:06,240 --> 00:41:09,140
Really?
It looked a bit suspicious earlier.

699
00:41:09,210 --> 00:41:11,540
- You were shielding her like this.
- Yes.

700
00:41:11,540 --> 00:41:15,010
Should I have just let her get hurt?
What am I, a savage?

701
00:41:15,440 --> 00:41:18,910
But how could I feel nothing
while being held by a man?

702
00:41:19,920 --> 00:41:22,720
The feeling's mutual.
Were you my brother in a past life?

703
00:41:23,220 --> 00:41:24,250
Did you hear that?

704
00:41:24,750 --> 00:41:26,620
Did you know Jun Hyeok calls me
"brother" sometimes?

705
00:41:27,520 --> 00:41:28,520
All right, listen up.

706
00:41:29,020 --> 00:41:30,390
Let's get back to our meeting, okay?

707
00:41:30,860 --> 00:41:33,000
What are you going to do?
Every time I see Dr. Han,

708
00:41:33,060 --> 00:41:36,100
I feel so guilty for tricking her
into thinking I'm Ju Ah's boyfriend.

709
00:41:36,300 --> 00:41:39,670
What else can you do? Break up.
Just dump her, Jun Hyeok.

710
00:41:39,900 --> 00:41:42,270
Right.
So Mom won't give you a hard time.

711
00:41:42,270 --> 00:41:46,310
- Yes.
- Before the show... We are through.

712
00:41:47,080 --> 00:41:50,380
You little... Then are you going to
announce right away...

713
00:41:50,510 --> 00:41:51,810
that you two are dating?

714
00:41:52,210 --> 00:41:53,620
It'll be difficult to do it
right away.

715
00:41:54,050 --> 00:41:56,350
Why? They've decided to do the show.

716
00:41:56,620 --> 00:41:57,820
Then they'll probably make up.

717
00:41:58,090 --> 00:42:01,860
They're just collaborating
as business partners.

718
00:42:02,260 --> 00:42:05,160
Oh, man.
Does that shoot start next week?

719
00:42:05,290 --> 00:42:09,430
Yes. I'm worried
a fight is going to break out.

720
00:42:10,030 --> 00:42:12,970
That sounds exciting.
Can I go watch them fight?

721
00:42:17,940 --> 00:42:18,970
(Onjeong Traditional Market)

722
00:42:22,040 --> 00:42:24,280
(Gong Myeong Jeong Dae Han Clinic)

723
00:42:26,820 --> 00:42:27,920
(Sunny Korean Medicine Clinic)

724
00:42:39,330 --> 00:42:41,030
Thank you for coming out so early.

725
00:42:41,360 --> 00:42:43,930
(Hope Stationery and Supermarket)

726
00:42:44,530 --> 00:42:45,830
You do these exercises every day?

727
00:42:46,340 --> 00:42:50,710
Oh, yes.
To promote the vendors' health,

728
00:42:50,870 --> 00:42:53,340
I developed this program myself.

729
00:42:54,580 --> 00:42:59,050
It's the Healthy Workplace Project.
Five minutes to reenergize your day.

730
00:43:00,180 --> 00:43:01,180
I see.

731
00:43:01,950 --> 00:43:05,350
Yes, if you stretch out like this
before starting your day,

732
00:43:05,620 --> 00:43:07,760
it makes the whole day go by
much more easily.

733
00:43:08,060 --> 00:43:11,260
We help each other stretch
and exchange friendly greetings,

734
00:43:11,330 --> 00:43:13,900
and the idea is
to build teamwork, too.

735
00:43:14,300 --> 00:43:15,300
Yes, that's right.

736
00:43:15,760 --> 00:43:18,700
Everyone, let's get started.

737
00:43:19,100 --> 00:43:23,570
First, let's get into position.
Spread your feet shoulder-width.

738
00:43:23,640 --> 00:43:25,140
That's it, shoulder-width.

739
00:43:25,640 --> 00:43:26,640
My gosh!

740
00:43:26,910 --> 00:43:27,940
Hey, easy there...

741
00:43:27,940 --> 00:43:29,240
- Oh, I'm giving him a massage.
- Yes.

742
00:43:29,240 --> 00:43:30,310
This is a pressure point for colds.

743
00:43:33,380 --> 00:43:36,750
- You can start when you're ready.
- Yes. Okay.

744
00:43:37,320 --> 00:43:39,690
And now...

745
00:43:39,760 --> 00:43:42,560
Let the Onjeong exercises begin!

746
00:43:50,670 --> 00:43:52,970
I love you!

747
00:43:53,100 --> 00:43:54,700
Onjeong!

748
00:44:01,640 --> 00:44:05,110
We want to film
the Merchants' Association today.

749
00:44:05,110 --> 00:44:06,250
What's your schedule like?

750
00:44:06,820 --> 00:44:08,820
Today, before I open my clinic,

751
00:44:09,490 --> 00:44:11,750
we're starting
with a clean-up of the area...

752
00:44:11,750 --> 00:44:14,260
And at lunchtime,
we'll be disinfecting the area.

753
00:44:14,460 --> 00:44:16,260
You do that yourselves?

754
00:44:16,630 --> 00:44:19,460
Yes. In addition to what
the professional service does,

755
00:44:19,560 --> 00:44:21,560
the Merchants' Association does
its own disinfecting periodically...

756
00:44:21,630 --> 00:44:24,370
Yes, that's right.
To step up our hygiene measures,

757
00:44:24,500 --> 00:44:28,300
I'm the one who brought in
this advanced disinfection system.

758
00:44:28,570 --> 00:44:31,810
Please make sure you mention that
in the narration.

759
00:44:32,410 --> 00:44:36,150
All right. We'll be sure to capture
your dedication to the market.

760
00:44:37,010 --> 00:44:40,450
Excuse me, Director?
My right side is my best angle.

761
00:44:40,680 --> 00:44:42,220
From the right side, if possible.

762
00:44:43,090 --> 00:44:45,120
- Sure. Noted.
- I'd appreciate it.

763
00:44:45,120 --> 00:44:48,020
- All right.
- We'll step out and get set up.

764
00:44:48,320 --> 00:44:50,360
- Sure.
- See you in a bit, then.

765
00:44:50,430 --> 00:44:52,590
- See you in a bit.
- Okay.

766
00:44:52,660 --> 00:44:54,130
- Hello.
- Hello.

767
00:44:55,030 --> 00:44:58,030
"My right side is my best angle."
Hey, give me a break.

768
00:44:58,230 --> 00:44:59,700
With a face like yours,
what difference does it make?

769
00:45:00,000 --> 00:45:02,570
Look who's talking.
With a face as plain as yours,

770
00:45:02,870 --> 00:45:05,170
it looks fairly the same
from both sides.

771
00:45:05,170 --> 00:45:07,940
Hey! If you butt in again,
you'll be sorry.

772
00:45:07,940 --> 00:45:10,450
What? My right side is a work of art
like Agrippa, you punk.

773
00:45:10,680 --> 00:45:12,750
I doubt you know who Agrippa is.
Good grief.

774
00:45:12,820 --> 00:45:15,750
- Do it fairly, like your face.
- Oh, boy.

775
00:45:17,150 --> 00:45:21,120
- Look at all this trash. Oh, dear.
- Right, yes.

776
00:45:22,990 --> 00:45:25,890
Picking up trash again today
to keep Onjeong Market clean!

777
00:45:27,700 --> 00:45:31,370
Like this.
Good grief, all this trash.

778
00:45:32,970 --> 00:45:34,000
Oh, boy.

779
00:45:34,400 --> 00:45:36,340
Gosh, I can't believe
someone just threw this out.

780
00:45:36,510 --> 00:45:37,510
Leaving trash like this.

781
00:45:37,770 --> 00:45:38,770
Oh, dear.

782
00:45:39,480 --> 00:45:40,840
My gosh, just look at this mess.

783
00:45:41,510 --> 00:45:45,210
Oh, who leaves big junk like this
lying around? Goodness.

784
00:45:45,410 --> 00:45:48,850
We can't let our dear VP get hurt!
Mr. Vice President?

785
00:45:49,020 --> 00:45:51,250
Take my hand.

786
00:45:52,220 --> 00:45:55,690
See? This is how we help one another
during our community service. Yes.

787
00:45:55,690 --> 00:45:57,390
We've got to clean spots like this
really well.

788
00:45:57,390 --> 00:45:58,860
Hey! What are you doing?

789
00:45:59,960 --> 00:46:02,160
No, it's fine.
I can clean this area myself.

790
00:46:02,160 --> 00:46:03,400
- Director, let's go over there.
- Right here.

791
00:46:03,400 --> 00:46:05,300
I know a prime spot
for spraying the disinfectant.

792
00:46:05,370 --> 00:46:06,600
Come on, this way.

793
00:46:06,870 --> 00:46:10,340
But this spot is the dirtiest.
No, really, right here. This is it.

794
00:46:10,340 --> 00:46:12,670
- Hey! We need to clean here.
- Go over there, you punk.

795
00:46:12,740 --> 00:46:14,580
- We must do this spot, right here!
- My gosh, you're such a pest.

796
00:46:14,640 --> 00:46:15,940
This spot is perfect. It's perfect!

797
00:46:16,010 --> 00:46:18,450
- I ought to... Just do it right!
- Hey, guys!

798
00:46:18,450 --> 00:46:20,580
- Goodness.
- Guys, the cameras!

799
00:46:21,080 --> 00:46:22,180
The cameras? Right.

800
00:46:23,820 --> 00:46:25,720
- Oh, dear!
- There are many bugs around here.

801
00:46:25,750 --> 00:46:27,320
- Tell me about it.
- Just like this.

802
00:46:27,320 --> 00:46:29,090
- We should do a great job.
- Yes, we should.

803
00:46:29,160 --> 00:46:31,290
- My gosh.
- Time for some pest extermination.

804
00:46:31,360 --> 00:46:33,430
There are some very big pests
in this world.

805
00:46:33,500 --> 00:46:35,860
- You shouldn't live like a pest.
- And you need skill to catch them.

806
00:46:43,540 --> 00:46:44,870
Hello, there.

807
00:46:45,910 --> 00:46:46,910
Please, come in.

808
00:46:47,740 --> 00:46:50,380
Come on in.
Let me get you something to drink...

809
00:46:50,680 --> 00:46:52,680
- Please, come on in.
- No, it's okay.

810
00:46:52,920 --> 00:46:56,390
I hope the shoot goes off
without a hitch. I'm worried.

811
00:46:56,450 --> 00:46:57,450
I know.

812
00:46:57,990 --> 00:47:00,020
Tell me about it.
Gosh, the more I see them,

813
00:47:00,090 --> 00:47:01,760
the less confident I am
that I can get them to make up.

814
00:47:02,190 --> 00:47:06,330
I know. During that workout,
the two doctors were about to fight.

815
00:47:06,460 --> 00:47:10,000
- Oh, boy.
- This is a real mess. Man.

816
00:47:11,300 --> 00:47:13,200
So, why did you turn down
our Jin Ah?

817
00:47:13,800 --> 00:47:14,800
Are you seeing someone else?

818
00:47:16,610 --> 00:47:18,470
No, I'm not. There's no one.

819
00:47:18,740 --> 00:47:19,910
Then why?

820
00:47:20,680 --> 00:47:22,140
It's just that...

821
00:47:23,150 --> 00:47:24,310
Well, it was...

822
00:47:25,310 --> 00:47:27,420
When I became a cop,

823
00:47:28,220 --> 00:47:30,890
I made a promise to myself
not to date or get married.

824
00:47:31,220 --> 00:47:33,660
What's being a cop got to do
with dating?

825
00:47:36,230 --> 00:47:38,430
My father was a police officer, too.

826
00:47:38,760 --> 00:47:39,760
Okay.

827
00:47:40,330 --> 00:47:42,630
He passed away
when I was really young.

828
00:47:43,130 --> 00:47:44,200
So...

829
00:47:45,170 --> 00:47:49,570
Did it happen
while he was working a case?

830
00:47:49,670 --> 00:47:51,370
Yes, while chasing a suspect.

831
00:47:51,670 --> 00:47:52,670
I see.

832
00:47:53,910 --> 00:47:55,940
And my mother...

833
00:47:56,310 --> 00:47:58,510
I watched her struggle
to raise me all on her own.

834
00:47:59,880 --> 00:48:01,120
I just don't want someone I love...

835
00:48:01,850 --> 00:48:04,090
to end up unhappy because of me.

836
00:48:05,550 --> 00:48:06,760
If I'm not confident
I can prevent that,

837
00:48:07,060 --> 00:48:08,990
I figure it's better
not to start anything at all.

838
00:48:10,060 --> 00:48:14,330
But I can't seem to help
the way I feel.

839
00:48:15,460 --> 00:48:16,470
I'll be more careful.

840
00:48:19,170 --> 00:48:20,170
I see what you mean.

841
00:48:21,400 --> 00:48:22,500
That makes sense. You're right.

842
00:48:23,240 --> 00:48:25,310
- Right.
- Hang in there.

843
00:48:27,680 --> 00:48:30,050
(My Endorphin)

844
00:48:38,750 --> 00:48:42,690
The way they growl at each other
when the cameras are off.

845
00:48:42,860 --> 00:48:44,290
It's quite a spectacle.

846
00:48:45,160 --> 00:48:46,630
I guess that's a skill in itself.

847
00:48:46,930 --> 00:48:48,260
I really ought to give him
a piece of my mind.

848
00:48:49,200 --> 00:48:51,630
What was Uncle even doing?
He couldn't get them to make up.

849
00:48:51,870 --> 00:48:54,540
Why would he?
It's all for show, anyway.

850
00:48:55,070 --> 00:48:57,340
I have zero intention
of making up with them.

851
00:49:05,280 --> 00:49:06,680
Unbelievable.

852
00:49:08,020 --> 00:49:10,250
I'm really starting to lose hope.
Seriously.

853
00:49:26,270 --> 00:49:28,700
What the heck?
He hasn't even called.

854
00:49:31,510 --> 00:49:34,810
Is he giving up on me
because our brothers can't make up?

855
00:49:43,450 --> 00:49:44,920
Don't cause any trouble today,
and do this right.

856
00:49:45,290 --> 00:49:46,290
I'll be watching you.

857
00:49:46,960 --> 00:49:47,960
Okay.

858
00:49:50,560 --> 00:49:52,260
Oh, why are you down here alone?
Where's your mom?

859
00:49:53,730 --> 00:49:56,930
She can't make it for meals anymore.
She gets off work late.

860
00:49:57,030 --> 00:49:59,630
Yes, it must be tough,
doing work she's not used to.

861
00:49:59,940 --> 00:50:02,340
Let's let her sleep in.
I'll get her food when she wakes up.

862
00:50:03,170 --> 00:50:05,610
I work just as hard as Auntie.
Oh, boy.

863
00:50:06,210 --> 00:50:07,210
What was that?

864
00:50:09,810 --> 00:50:14,020
I mean, I'm on my feet all day
at the bookstore, so I'm tired too.

865
00:50:15,580 --> 00:50:17,950
By the way, I'm going to see
the store I'm taking over today.

866
00:50:18,920 --> 00:50:20,220
Will you be okay on your own?

867
00:50:20,990 --> 00:50:23,060
- Want me to come with you?
- You're busy with the shoot.

868
00:50:23,060 --> 00:50:24,430
And you have an interview today.

869
00:50:24,560 --> 00:50:26,060
I'll be fine by myself.

870
00:50:26,530 --> 00:50:28,930
Take Min Seo with you.
She's free. Right?

871
00:50:29,600 --> 00:50:30,730
Will that be okay with you?

872
00:50:31,070 --> 00:50:33,570
Yes, I have a club activity,
so I'll be home late anyway.

873
00:50:34,470 --> 00:50:38,270
Wow, this grilled fish is amazing.
But why does it taste like curry?

874
00:50:38,670 --> 00:50:40,380
Because I added curry powder.

875
00:50:40,740 --> 00:50:43,880
It gets rid of the fishy smell
and adds a nice flavor. You like it?

876
00:50:44,680 --> 00:50:47,050
- You made this?
- Yes.

877
00:50:47,850 --> 00:50:50,250
She's not our kid, but she's really
got her act together.

878
00:50:50,890 --> 00:50:54,960
Tell me about it.
She's nothing like my daughter.

879
00:51:07,540 --> 00:51:09,170
Hey, Eun Bin...

880
00:51:09,540 --> 00:51:12,270
Were you upset earlier
when they were comparing us?

881
00:51:13,210 --> 00:51:15,110
They were right,
so why would I be upset?

882
00:51:20,350 --> 00:51:22,480
Can you do my eyeliner
like you do yours?

883
00:51:23,890 --> 00:51:25,650
But you're way better
at makeup than I am.

884
00:51:26,150 --> 00:51:27,760
I just want to be more like you.

885
00:51:28,320 --> 00:51:30,630
Me? Why?

886
00:51:31,530 --> 00:51:35,760
Everyone likes you.
My family and even Woo Jae.

887
00:51:39,700 --> 00:51:40,870
You know...

888
00:51:41,500 --> 00:51:45,340
Back in the second grade,
I found out that I was adopted.

889
00:51:46,640 --> 00:51:48,910
- You did?
- Yes.

890
00:51:49,810 --> 00:51:51,580
And ever since then, every night...

891
00:51:52,380 --> 00:51:54,350
I'd have dreams about
being thrown out of the house.

892
00:51:56,080 --> 00:51:57,990
I felt the same way you do.

893
00:51:58,690 --> 00:52:01,360
My own birth mother abandoned me,

894
00:52:02,520 --> 00:52:06,630
and I felt like my adoptive parents
could abandon me at any moment too.

895
00:52:08,760 --> 00:52:12,470
So I tried so hard to be liked...

896
00:52:13,400 --> 00:52:15,600
that now I'm nice to everyone
out of habit.

897
00:52:17,840 --> 00:52:18,970
I had no idea.

898
00:52:21,240 --> 00:52:24,810
So, will you meet your birth mom
before you go back to the US?

899
00:52:27,420 --> 00:52:29,650
Who knows?
I might've already met her.

900
00:52:30,520 --> 00:52:35,220
True. If you don't recognize her,
you could've met her and not known.

901
00:52:35,460 --> 00:52:36,460
Right.

902
00:52:46,370 --> 00:52:49,540
Hey, look at me.
Notice anything different?

903
00:52:50,040 --> 00:52:51,570
No idea.

904
00:52:52,570 --> 00:52:55,580
I made my eyeliner subtle,
like Min Seo's.

905
00:52:56,880 --> 00:52:59,380
I don't even know what eyeliner is.

906
00:53:06,020 --> 00:53:08,690
You're like a fresh head of lettuce.

907
00:53:09,390 --> 00:53:11,360
- Lettuce?
- Yes, lettuce.

908
00:53:11,760 --> 00:53:13,130
Lettuce is my favorite.

909
00:53:21,900 --> 00:53:23,270
What's going on here?

910
00:53:23,770 --> 00:53:25,010
Auntie! Woo Jae!

911
00:53:27,010 --> 00:53:31,380
- Why? Gosh, what's happening?
- I think there's a leak.

912
00:53:31,710 --> 00:53:33,110
We've got our own swimming pool now.

913
00:53:33,720 --> 00:53:35,780
The drain pipe joint
that came apart the other day...

914
00:53:36,050 --> 00:53:39,090
I put waterproof tape on it.
It probably got wet and fell off.

915
00:53:39,920 --> 00:53:42,660
What are we going to do?
The plumber can only come tomorrow.

916
00:53:43,160 --> 00:53:45,460
Sorry, I wish I could help.

917
00:53:45,690 --> 00:53:48,260
You?
All you know how to do is study.

918
00:53:48,460 --> 00:53:51,370
Can you two clean this up for now?
I'll try calling another plumber.

919
00:53:51,470 --> 00:53:53,570
On second thought,
it'll be faster if I go find one.

920
00:53:54,940 --> 00:53:56,000
Okay.

921
00:54:03,040 --> 00:54:04,980
Uncle, are you busy right now?

922
00:54:06,580 --> 00:54:09,280
Okay, since we've got a handle
on the stage concept,

923
00:54:09,750 --> 00:54:13,460
let's choose a head director
to lead the launch show production.

924
00:54:13,990 --> 00:54:16,120
Ms. Gong,
why don't you take the lead?

925
00:54:16,830 --> 00:54:17,830
Me?

926
00:54:18,530 --> 00:54:21,930
Since it's your concept,
you'd be the best one to direct it.

927
00:54:23,060 --> 00:54:24,130
I agree.

928
00:54:24,930 --> 00:54:26,670
Mr. Park, you don't want to do it?

929
00:54:26,770 --> 00:54:29,900
Gosh, not me.
It's your chance to prove yourself.

930
00:54:29,900 --> 00:54:31,870
It's time to finally shake
that "med school grad" label.

931
00:54:32,240 --> 00:54:34,140
I'll back you up all the way.

932
00:54:35,280 --> 00:54:39,280
Then let's give Ms. Gong
a round of applause to show support.

933
00:54:41,180 --> 00:54:42,580
We're counting on you.

934
00:54:43,850 --> 00:54:46,860
Thanks, everyone.
So your designs can truly shine...

935
00:54:46,920 --> 00:54:48,320
I will do my absolute best.

936
00:54:50,330 --> 00:54:53,730
Dr. Han should be here soon.
Let's wrap up for today.

937
00:54:54,030 --> 00:54:55,030
- Okay.
- Right.

938
00:55:01,600 --> 00:55:04,340
When Dr. Han gets here,
make sure you stick to the plan.

939
00:55:05,240 --> 00:55:08,080
Don't worry, just watch me.
I'm coming at you.

940
00:55:09,410 --> 00:55:11,610
So I just have to
stir things up, right?

941
00:55:16,420 --> 00:55:18,990
These are the outfits you'll wear
on the runway, Doctor.

942
00:55:21,320 --> 00:55:25,160
During your fitting today,
we'll also test your runway walk.

943
00:55:26,390 --> 00:55:29,830
I'm not a professional model,
so I'm worried I won't walk well.

944
00:55:31,130 --> 00:55:35,040
If you'd like, we can set you up
with a professional coach.

945
00:55:35,640 --> 00:55:36,870
Oh, could you do that for me?

946
00:55:37,570 --> 00:55:40,210
It's so reassuring to have you here,
Mr. Park.

947
00:55:41,240 --> 00:55:42,380
Don't worry about a thing.

948
00:55:49,020 --> 00:55:51,150
Even during
the launch show rehearsal,

949
00:55:51,220 --> 00:55:53,990
I'll check your timing
and give you the cue personally.

950
00:55:55,060 --> 00:55:58,760
Mr. Park, are you trying
to step on my toes as a director?

951
00:56:00,030 --> 00:56:02,360
What do you mean, step on your toes?
We're a team.

952
00:56:02,760 --> 00:56:03,830
It's not like
we have set territories.

953
00:56:03,830 --> 00:56:07,270
Are you an amateur? Don't you know
that mixed signals cause confusion?

954
00:56:07,740 --> 00:56:08,740
Unbelievable.

955
00:56:09,070 --> 00:56:10,070
Seriously.

956
00:56:13,270 --> 00:56:17,050
Hey, Dr. Han is here.
Can you two knock it off?

957
00:56:17,250 --> 00:56:18,680
You two have been fighting
all the time lately.

958
00:56:19,850 --> 00:56:21,020
I'm sorry, Director.

959
00:56:21,680 --> 00:56:22,820
So irritating.

960
00:56:24,120 --> 00:56:25,950
Doctor, shall we go get you fitted?

961
00:56:27,920 --> 00:56:28,920
My goodness.

962
00:56:29,720 --> 00:56:30,760
Good grief.

963
00:56:32,390 --> 00:56:33,390
Honestly.

964
00:56:34,960 --> 00:56:35,960
Man...

965
00:56:48,010 --> 00:56:49,010
Hey.

966
00:56:49,580 --> 00:56:52,410
Why are you so harsh with Jun Hyeok?

967
00:56:52,610 --> 00:56:54,980
Because he keeps blurring the lines
between work and our personal life.

968
00:56:55,050 --> 00:56:56,750
Then talk to him nicely.

969
00:56:57,190 --> 00:57:00,390
When you use that accusatory tone,
your point doesn't get across,

970
00:57:00,690 --> 00:57:02,220
and you'll just end up
hurting his feelings.

971
00:57:02,390 --> 00:57:06,260
Whatever. If he keeps this up,
I'm going to break up with him.

972
00:57:06,860 --> 00:57:08,260
Why are you being so dramatic?

973
00:57:08,500 --> 00:57:10,230
If you felt that way, why did you
have him meet the family?

974
00:57:10,230 --> 00:57:12,800
- You told me to bring him over.
- What?

975
00:57:16,770 --> 00:57:18,710
Anyway, is this really my size?

976
00:57:19,270 --> 00:57:20,510
Why? Is it uncomfortable?

977
00:57:21,180 --> 00:57:22,710
You're not just picking a fight
with me, are you?

978
00:57:22,910 --> 00:57:24,110
Of course not.

979
00:57:24,980 --> 00:57:26,980
It just feels a little tight.

980
00:57:27,550 --> 00:57:30,590
You keep saying you're tired,
but you're gaining weight just fine.

981
00:57:30,590 --> 00:57:33,760
I'm the type who gains weight
when I'm tired.

982
00:57:33,890 --> 00:57:37,060
Yes, ma'am.
We'll be sure to let it out for you.

983
00:57:37,760 --> 00:57:38,890
Let's just go.

984
00:57:40,030 --> 00:57:41,830
Honestly, that girl.

985
00:57:45,000 --> 00:57:49,800
I'm free anytime.
Whenever works for you, Sister.

986
00:57:51,210 --> 00:57:53,980
Okay, I understand.
Please let me know.

987
00:57:54,610 --> 00:57:55,610
Okay.

988
00:58:00,380 --> 00:58:02,850
So the person you wanted to see
was the Sister?

989
00:58:03,920 --> 00:58:04,920
Yes.

990
00:58:05,550 --> 00:58:07,690
She must be someone special to you.

991
00:58:08,390 --> 00:58:11,330
She is. Ready to go? I'm all set.

992
00:58:11,860 --> 00:58:12,960
Yes, let's go.

993
00:58:14,200 --> 00:58:15,960
(3H Acupressure Bed)

994
00:58:17,100 --> 00:58:18,330
What do you think
of the store's vibe?

995
00:58:19,100 --> 00:58:22,440
It's very classy.
It really fits your image perfectly.

996
00:58:23,240 --> 00:58:24,810
Are you here to look around?

997
00:58:26,270 --> 00:58:30,140
Yes, to see the store layout
and the customer flow.

998
00:58:30,510 --> 00:58:34,550
Excuse me, would it be okay
if I take a video of the store?

999
00:58:36,180 --> 00:58:38,750
I thought everyone else back home
would be curious to see it.

1000
00:58:39,420 --> 00:58:41,420
That's a wonderful idea.

1001
00:58:41,760 --> 00:58:42,820
Please, feel free to look around.

1002
00:58:43,420 --> 00:58:44,460
Thank you.

1003
00:58:46,160 --> 00:58:47,400
She must be your daughter.

1004
00:58:48,530 --> 00:58:49,900
I get that a lot.

1005
00:59:08,850 --> 00:59:13,520
I went to the main intersection,
but they had no repairmen. What now?

1006
00:59:14,390 --> 00:59:15,760
Why weren't you answering
your phone?

1007
00:59:16,090 --> 00:59:17,530
What? My phone?

1008
00:59:19,430 --> 00:59:22,600
- You did call.
- Anyway, it's fixed. Don't worry.

1009
00:59:22,760 --> 00:59:23,870
Fixed? How?

1010
00:59:24,670 --> 00:59:28,070
My uncle is handy with this stuff.
He came earlier, fixed it, and left.

1011
00:59:28,640 --> 00:59:29,740
He already left?

1012
00:59:31,270 --> 00:59:32,270
Yes.

1013
00:59:34,480 --> 00:59:37,080
Did he leave a message
for me or anything?

1014
00:59:37,710 --> 00:59:38,850
No, he didn't.

1015
00:59:59,200 --> 01:00:00,270
Hey, Dong Suk.

1016
01:00:02,240 --> 01:00:03,240
What's that?

1017
01:00:03,940 --> 01:00:06,980
Hey! Dong Suk, what's wrong?

1018
01:00:07,880 --> 01:00:08,880
What's wrong?

1019
01:00:09,110 --> 01:00:10,710
What, is something wrong
with the sink?

1020
01:00:14,880 --> 01:00:16,320
Am I less important to you
than a sink?

1021
01:00:16,990 --> 01:00:17,990
What?

1022
01:00:17,990 --> 01:00:19,220
Why didn't you call me?

1023
01:00:19,220 --> 01:00:21,090
If you stopped by,
you should've waited for me.

1024
01:00:21,160 --> 01:00:24,730
Why did you leave right away?
I wanted to see you too, you know.

1025
01:00:25,090 --> 01:00:26,090
What?

1026
01:00:27,230 --> 01:00:31,530
You were so crazy about me before.
What, did the kiss change your mind?

1027
01:00:31,600 --> 01:00:33,630
You don't care
if our brothers make up?

1028
01:00:34,600 --> 01:00:35,900
You've got it all wrong, Dong Suk.

1029
01:00:37,210 --> 01:00:38,440
It's not like that.

1030
01:00:39,740 --> 01:00:44,210
- Why are you laughing? Is it funny?
- No, that's not why.

1031
01:00:45,210 --> 01:00:47,080
It's because I'm happy to see you.
That's why.

1032
01:00:52,420 --> 01:00:53,860
(What's Grammar)

1033
01:00:54,960 --> 01:00:59,590
Wow, bookstores and school stuff...
It's been forever. I'm so excited.

1034
01:00:59,930 --> 01:01:04,230
If you're this excited to study,
you've already won half the battle.

1035
01:01:07,040 --> 01:01:10,270
- Can I ask you for a favor?
- Yes.

1036
01:01:11,040 --> 01:01:14,610
Can you keep my English studies
a secret from my family?

1037
01:01:15,380 --> 01:01:16,380
Of course.

1038
01:01:17,780 --> 01:01:19,510
I promised to buy you
something delicious.

1039
01:01:19,510 --> 01:01:20,880
Just tteokbokki?

1040
01:01:21,250 --> 01:01:24,750
Actually, this is the whole reason
I came to Onjeong.

1041
01:01:25,450 --> 01:01:28,490
I'm on a quest to find
the best tteokbokki in the country.

1042
01:01:28,960 --> 01:01:30,160
I see.

1043
01:01:31,430 --> 01:01:32,590
What can I get for you?

1044
01:01:34,260 --> 01:01:36,960
- Ma'am, what's next?
- These three here.

1045
01:01:40,230 --> 01:01:42,040
What? Jeong Sun.

1046
01:01:44,770 --> 01:01:46,540
You are Jeong Sun, right?

1047
01:01:50,210 --> 01:01:51,210
Im Jeong Sun.

1048
01:01:54,680 --> 01:01:55,920
Oh, Seong Mi.

1049
01:01:56,380 --> 01:01:59,220
Everyone's busy
with work and the shoot,

1050
01:01:59,220 --> 01:02:00,690
so it's just the two of us.

1051
01:02:01,020 --> 01:02:05,190
What should we do for dinner?
Should we order in?

1052
01:02:05,460 --> 01:02:08,160
Oh, I'm so sorry, Mother.

1053
01:02:08,460 --> 01:02:11,500
A friend dropped by unexpectedly,
so I'm having dinner with her.

1054
01:02:11,570 --> 01:02:15,500
That's fine, dear. That's good.
You need to see your friends.

1055
01:02:15,740 --> 01:02:17,610
Take your time and have fun.

1056
01:02:18,710 --> 01:02:22,340
No, it's just a quick dinner,
so I'll be home soon.

1057
01:02:22,840 --> 01:02:24,210
Wait for me, Mother.

1058
01:02:24,750 --> 01:02:25,750
Okay.

1059
01:02:28,880 --> 01:02:30,620
I totally forgot to call.

1060
01:02:31,450 --> 01:02:33,990
Don't most women
call their husbands?

1061
01:02:34,520 --> 01:02:35,620
Whatever.

1062
01:02:37,490 --> 01:02:41,060
So, spill it. What's so important
you had to ask me out to dinner?

1063
01:02:44,400 --> 01:02:46,270
Lately, I've been telling people...

1064
01:02:46,570 --> 01:02:49,940
that they should get a body scrub
at a Korean spa.

1065
01:02:50,910 --> 01:02:53,440
- Why?
- Things like lumps...

1066
01:02:53,880 --> 01:02:55,880
The people who are most likely
to find them first...

1067
01:02:56,380 --> 01:02:57,680
are the scrub attendants.

1068
01:02:58,480 --> 01:03:01,780
Are my TSH levels off?

1069
01:03:02,480 --> 01:03:06,320
- Is anything wrong with my thyroid?
- No, your thyroid is fine.

1070
01:03:07,050 --> 01:03:08,060
Then what is it?

1071
01:03:08,360 --> 01:03:12,130
When I ran your blood tests,
I also ran the tumor markers,

1072
01:03:13,560 --> 01:03:15,160
and the breast cancer markers
came back high.

1073
01:03:20,400 --> 01:03:23,000
How far out of the reference range?

1074
01:03:25,040 --> 01:03:26,270
Significantly.

1075
01:03:28,540 --> 01:03:31,810
I'll come in tomorrow.
Let's do an ultrasound first.

1076
01:03:32,210 --> 01:03:34,950
Okay. And a biopsy if we need to.

1077
01:03:37,420 --> 01:03:38,920
I'm worried sick.

1078
01:03:40,120 --> 01:03:42,890
It's not a definitive diagnosis,
and the results aren't back yet.

1079
01:03:42,960 --> 01:03:44,460
How can a doctor
be acting like this?

1080
01:03:44,930 --> 01:03:48,260
Jumping to the worst-case scenario
is a sign of an anxiety disorder.

1081
01:03:50,670 --> 01:03:51,670
Let's eat.

1082
01:04:13,190 --> 01:04:14,520
It's okay, Seong Mi.

1083
01:04:17,060 --> 01:04:18,490
It's probably nothing.

1084
01:04:54,630 --> 01:04:57,270
(Recipe For Love)

1085
01:04:57,330 --> 01:05:00,840
She's my source of inspiration.
My muse, if you will.

1086
01:05:00,900 --> 01:05:03,370
You should quit your clinic
and become an actor.

1087
01:05:03,370 --> 01:05:04,570
Your acting is just...

1088
01:05:04,570 --> 01:05:07,340
- It's worthy of a Best Actor Award.
- I know, right?

1089
01:05:07,540 --> 01:05:09,780
It's nice to be out
with our grandkids.

1090
01:05:09,840 --> 01:05:11,680
This is a first for me,
coming to a place like this.

1091
01:05:11,750 --> 01:05:13,510
I'll bring you here more often,
Grandpa.

1092
01:05:13,650 --> 01:05:18,490
You can still see the love
in his gaze when he looks at Ju Ah.

1093
01:05:18,690 --> 01:05:21,620
They say a man
never forgets his first love.

1094
01:05:24,430 --> 01:05:27,300
Make a bucket list.
I'll make it all happen.

1095
01:05:27,830 --> 01:05:31,470
- Did you make one?
- There, my bucket list.
